The paper deals with the size of the LZ77 encoding, which is a data compression technique. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms for constructing the LZ77 encoding, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the tightness of bounds, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the encoding of non-constant alphabets, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
